shortText: Saini to Umran Malik, (no ball) SIX

preText:
7.30pm Mohammed Siraj to open the bowling for RCB. Rohit and Ishan are in the middle. One slip

The teams are observing a two-minute silence for Salim Durani, who died this morning.

Parth: "Can't even a regular substitute come apart from the names given in the list?" --- No, and that has always been the case.

Shyam: "Who is Nehal Wadhera and Arshad Khan? 2 new finds of MI scouting network?" --- Nehal Wadhera is a hard-hitting left-hand Punjab batter who can bowl some legspin as well. Arshad Khan is an MP allrounder, bats left-hand and bowls left-arm seam. Both are making their T20 debut as well. Sampath tells me last time a team had two T20 debutants in an IPL game was Delhi Daredevils in 2018 (Sandeep Lammichane and Abhishek Sharma). KKR had two T20 debuts in their first match of the same season (Shubman Gill and Shivam Mavi).

Mohd Irshad: "MI looking better on paper than last year, hope to see that on ground too."

Shyam: "How is David Willey a sub? Havent they already reached 4 player limit?" --- Yes, and that means he cannot be used as an Impact Player but if an overseas players goes off the field for a couple of overs, Willey can come in and field as a regular substitute.

Surath: "I don't get it! MI only playing 3 overseas players? And still no place for baby AB or Stubbs??? Why???" --- The fourth one - Jason Behrendorff - will be their Impact Player.

Mumbai Indians 1 Rohit Sharma (capt), 2 Ishan Kishan (wk), 3 Suryakumar Yadav, 4 Thilak Varma, 5 Tim David, 6 Cameron Green, 7 Nehal Wadhera, 8 Jofra Archer, 9 Hrithik Shokeen, 10 Arshad Khan, 11 Piyush Chawla
Substitutes: Jason Behrendorff, Vishnu Vinod, Shams Mulani, Sandeep Warrier, Ramandeep Singh

Royal Challengers Bangalore 1 Faf du Plessis (capt), 2 Virat Kohli, 3 Michael Bracewell, 4 Glenn Maxwell, 5 Shahbaz Ahmed, 6 Dinesh Karthik, 7 Harshal Patel, 8 Akash Deep, 9 Reece Topley, 10 Mohammed Siraj, 11 Karn Sharma
Substitutes: Anuj Rawat, Suyash Prabhudessai, Mahipal Lomror, Sonu Yadav, David Willey

DJDJ: "Why isn't Dewald Brevis playing in the 11. MI just wasting a top talent" --- With David being the more explosive of the two, it's difficult to see Brevis fitting in.

"With the new Impact Player rule, teams are backing themselves to chase," says Rohit Sharma. "The pitch looks good and we have to come out with the positive intent. Tim David, Cameron Green, Jofra Archer and Jason Behrendorff are our overseas players. We will try to correct the mistakes we made last time. There have been a few new faces as well in the side, so that will help. A great achievement to captain in 200 games."

7.00pm Rohit Sharma calls heads and tails it is. RCB have won the toss and they will be bowling first. "There was a bit of dew when we practised," Faf du Plessis says. "Our first goal is to make those playoffs, and follow the processes. Maxwell, Bracewell and Topley are our overseas players."

Talking about the dimensions, down the ground is 69 metres. And that's the longest boundary! One side is slightly shorter than the other.

6.50pm This is going to be a big season for Harshal too. He was supposed to be a key player for India at the T20 World Cup last year but didn't get to play even one game. An interview with Nagraj Gollapudi, he talked about not just that but also about the challenge of bowling on smaller grounds and to a player like Suryakumar Yadav. You can read the full interview here.

6.45pm Virat Kohli has just walked onto the field and the cheer for him is as loud as it could get. Harshal Patel is doing an interview with the host broadcaster on the sideline and isn't able to hear anything.

"Behrendorff and Mumbai will want to get into that middle order as soon as possible"

You can also try out ESPNcricinfo's first AR-based game - just aim and hit the stumps.

6.40pm If you are seeing this on a mobile device and didn't know it already, ESPNcricinfo is better experienced on our apps. And we have recently rolled out an update for Android, which you can download or update here.

Mumbai have been in a rebuilding phase since the 2022 mega auction. At that auction, they went in with a dream. The dream of having Jofra Archer and Jasprit Bumrah bowl in tandem for them. They knew their dream wouldn't become a reality immediately - Archer was not available for the 2022 season. But now with Bumrah out with a back injury, they will have to wait for yet another season. Having said that, they seemed to have got their batting might back. You can read more about what to expect from today's game in our preview.

RCB have been pretty consistent of late, making the playoffs in each of the last three seasons. This run has also coincided with them not playing at their home ground, M Chinnaswamy Stadium - theirs is one of the poorest home records for an IPL team. This season, they play six of their first eight games in Bengaluru, which could dictate how their campaign goes.

6.30pm Hello and welcome to the second game of Super Sunday. It's Royal Challengers Bangalore taking on Mumbai Indians in Bengaluru. RCB's quest for their maiden IPL title is still on, while Mumbai will be looking to bounce back after a forgettable 2022 season where they finished at the bottom of the points table.
postText: LG: "Technically this "impact player" is the same as "super sub" the ODIs used to have in early 2000s? " --- You can say so but there's one big difference. You had to name your XI and Supersub before the toss. Now the teams can name their XI after the toss and bring in an Impact Player from the list of substitutes anytime during the match.

postText:
What a way for RCB to start their campaign. They did not even need an Impact Player, such was their dominance. Hemant is working hard on his report, which should be up yet. The caravan rolls and we have Chennai Super Kings taking on Lucknow Super Giants tomorrow. Till then, this is Ashish Pant, signing off on behalf of Hemant, Ranjith and Raghav. Good night!

Faf du Plessis is the Player of the Match: It was a nice way to start the way we did in the powerplay. Siraj with his tail up is a beautiful thing. The bowler stuck to their task The last two or three overs, was a bit of learning. The cutters were working really well, it was not easy to hit the ball. There was value for your shots. Credit to the groundsman. Even the spinners found something. [On the crowd] It's awesome to play. It's my first time playing here as a home player, especially batting with Virat Kohli. [Fielding] You have to try and stay with the youngsters. I try and push the old hamstrings so that I can move in the field. To start the campaign with a bang, was huge.

Presentation time

Virat Kohli: Phenomenal win. Homecoming after so many years. Credit to their batters for getting to that score. Tilak batted well. We kept backing ourselves. Faf went first, and I joined later. I am very happy with how things went today. The new ball was a bit tricky, but we shifted the momentum by taking them down with the new ball. We nullified all their intensity. The wicket was quite a nice one. We hit good areas and kept putting pressure on the bowlers. [Crowd] Phenomenal, was a packed crowd. Every seat was full and we knew we would get a lot of support. We just ride off that intensity from the crowd They were right behind us. [On Karn Sharma] He was phenomenal, when he got that left-hander out, that was great bowling. He was bowling so well last year. He was ready to play. Even in the nets, he was not getting hit for sixes. He put us on the front foot right away. The first game of the IPL, and to perform like that was great. Apart from Mumbai winning five times and Chennai four times, we have qualified the most number of times, so we do play consistent cricket. It's just about staying focused, and just try to be the best balanced team. We need to play on this momentum. We just need to execute better.

Rohit Sharma: Didn't have a great start but was a good effort from Tilak at the end. But the bowlers didn't bowl well. We didn't bat good enough, it was a good pitch. [On Tilak] Some of the shorts he played today, he showed a lot of courage. We wanted to be courageous enough, and hats off to Tilak for getting us to the total. Was a good pitch to bat on. We did not bat to our potential. 30-40 runs would have been ideal. We were struggling t play the catch-up game. [No Bumrah] For the past six-eight months I am used to play without Bumrah. We can't control things which we can't control. The other guys are also talented. A lot of the guys haven't played IPL before. First game of the season, lot to look forward to.

Afeef: "A perfect return to the Chinnaswamy "

Shrikant : "I liked the move to send DK though it has not worked out. RCB is keeping an eye on NRR early on "

Neeraj : "Kohi wanted his own 'finishes off in style' moment..."

11.08pm Everything that could have gone right for RCB, did. Everything that could have wrong for Mumbai, did. Think that's the best way to put. Mumbai, bar Tilak Varma were all over the place, and still got to 171. But RCB openers, Virat Kohli and Faf du Plessis just showed how good a surface that was. The duo added 148 runs off 89 balls to set-up the chase. Kohli remained unbeaten on 82 off 49, while du Plessis scored 73 off 43. RCB mopped up the win in just 16.2 overs and that will give their net run-rate a boost.

preText:
7.29 pm Kyle Mayers has the new ball in hand. Slightly delayed start because a dog has run out onto the outfield... A mission by one person has now been joined by six ground staff members, the umpires and several players to try to usher it off the field but the dog is being extremely stubborn. However, the fans in the ground don't seem to mind. They're cheering the dog on wholeheartedly. MS Dhoni has a smile on his face watching it all unfold, as does Jadeja and Moeen Ali. The crowd has started chanting, "Doggy! Doggy! Doggy!" Give it a few more minutes and there will soon be a corporate sponsor for the dog. After a five-minute delay, we'll finally have the first ball.

7.01 pm The news is that Lucknow Super Giants have won the toss and will field first.

One change for LSG. Unadkat comes out and Yash Thakur comes in. CSK are unchanged.

Meanwhile Ben Stokes has had this to say down on the field when interviewed on TV: "Everything is coming on nicely. I feel like I've worked really hard to get to the place where I am at the moment with my knee. I think I might be able to turn the arm over tonight."

LSG XI: 1 KL Rahul (capt.), 2 Kyle Mayers, 3 Deepak Hooda, 4 Krunal Pandya, 5 Marcus Stoinis, 6 Nicholas Pooran (wk), 7 K Gowtham, 8 Avesh Khan, 9 Ravi Bishnoi, 10 Yash Thakur, 11 Mark Wood.

CSK XI: 1 Devon Conway, 2 Ruturaj Gaikwad, 3 Moeen Ali, 4 Ben Stokes, 5 Ambati Rayudu, 6 Shivam Dube, 7 Ravindra Jadeja, 8 MS Dhoni (capt/wk), 9 Mitchell Santner, 10 Deepak Chahar, 11 Rajvardhan Hangargekar.

6.30 pm Hello and welcome to ESPNcricinfo's live coverage of today's encounter in the 2023 Indian Premier League as the Chennai Super Kings host the Lucknow Super Giants. I'm Peter Della Penna and will be captaining the commentary ship solo throughout today's contest. To help set the scene for today's match, check out the match preview from Vishal Dikshit.

Karthik: "What are we waiting for?!! Let's GO! It's "Dhhoonnnii Dhonnii" time at the Chepauk! It's not about the match today, it's about the crazy emotions that flow like a huge wave! We don't know how much of it is left, but we'll take it all the same! "

Speaking of which, the Muthu brothers (yes, Alagappan and Deivarayan are related by blood) have penned this piece about relishing whatever time is left of the Dhoni era with CSK inside of Chepauk.

Ahead of the Asian Games and the Paris Olympics, this final appearance could be a very crucial learning.

postText:
9.23 pm CSK end on 217 for 7, and yet somehow their last 10 overs were slower than their first 10. The home crowd certainly got their money's worth for this innings. Can LSG chase this down? Stay tuned for the start of the chase.

CSK opener Devon Conway: "I think it was a great start for us tonight. The way Rutu played in that first six was pretty special and he took the pressure off me. He's sneaky strong. He times the ball and holds his shape really well, and he uses good bats. I think the slower ball into the wicket might be a good option for us, pace off and being unpredictable. I also felt for the spinners, some skidded on and some held up. It's a very special feeling [at Chepauk]. When I got here earlier, the crowd was special. They were pretty loud and it just creates a great atmosphere. Seeing MS Dhoni walk out there and do what he did and hearing the crowd is pretty special so it's good to be playing here in front of our fans. He said to go out, express yourself, enjoy, have fun and entertain."

For the IPL stats mavens out there, Dhoni completed 5,000 career IPL runs in his brief but belligerent innings.

Abhisek daga: "The way the entire chennai dressing room celebrated after dhoni hit the second six was just goosebumps written all over it... fantastic stuff..."

text: full on middle, charges this and launches a drive to wide long-on. Gaikwad leaps in the air to try to swat this back into play but it just barely clears him and thuds into the LCD ad boards.

postText: Anty: "@Arunabh, that is a compliment. If he was as reliable and dependable as a Honda, he would a mainstay in Indian cricket."

Strategic timeout taken.

Ricky: "The greatest mistake LSG can do is to drop Mayers when QDK comes in. Both are in supreme form. Maybe Stoinis to make place for them. But very few team got such a deadly balance in the history of IPL. Pure hitters and deadly pace with some good spin....."

text: massive strike! Full on fourth stump, winds up and launches this into the second tier over wide long-on.
postText: JB: "The famous CSK Chepauk spin web is on. This is what it's all about. From the days of Murali, Ashwin, Jakati to Jaddu, Moeen and Santner. Nothing has changed. Watch the overs go through in blitz speed now "

preText: Hangargekar comes into the attack for the first time replacing Moeen.

text: back of a length on fifth stump, tapped defensively to backward point for none.
in the slog on fourth stump, Pooran winds up and deposits a big heave eight rows back into the seats over midwicket.
137 kph length ball on the wide guideline, Pooran shuffles across to get in line and laces this behind point racing quickly to the rope.
full on eighth stump, Pooran winds up and creams this high over extra cover, two bounces to the rope.
postText: Sundar: "Why would they need to bring in Hangargekar at this juncture hen spin was doing so well! As an aside, I hope some bowling coaches work on him. His run up has very small strides and gives him absolutely no momentum whatsoever leading into the delivery stride."

Generous applause for Moeen after his spell ends.

postText: Nick: "Maybe unpopular but: I really don't get why Stoinis gets so many games around the world. Never seems settled in the crease and when used as an allrounder his bowling his very bland. Just off top of my head Hardie and Turner deserve more of a chance than Stoinis gets"

text: good length ball on seventh stump, goes for a big heave and misses.
shot of the day! Length ball on the wide guideline, Pooran cranks this flat over extra cover into the LCD ad boards.
quicker ball on a good length on seventh stump, Pooran winds up again but miscues a slog into his feet.

no no, this is the shot of the day! Reverse sweep into the front row of the third tier/upper deck! Full on off stump, Pooran premeditates getting into position to annihilate this over point. The crowd gasps at his brilliance coming up against a CSK legend.
good length ball on the legs, flicked behind square leg for one.
full and wide yorker, Pooran shuffles way outside off trying to scoop this over fine leg but miscues this straight to the fielder on the ring.
preText: Tushar Deshpande returns after a horror first over.

text: goes for wide yorker again, doesn't get it full enough and Pooran smokes a blistering drive flat to wide long-off. However, he doesn't get the elevation on it. Stokes on the boundary comes in initially before going back and takes a head height catch two yards in from the rope. If he's not there, it's thudding into the ads for six.
postText: Tomorrow, the league-stage champions of the past two seasons of the Indian Super League will go head-to-head for the ultimate prize: a chance to represent India in the Asian Champions League. But why do they have to do this? Who is playing? Find out right here.

text: length ball wide outside off, slapped past extra cover and Santner at cover sweeper has to work hard to track it down to save two runs.
Chahar gets punished after being challenged to attack the stumps! Full on middle, Gowtham winds up and clobbers this high and deep over midwicket.
another wide yorker speared outside the guideline. Wide called for the third ball in a row. Crowd groans.
length ball pushed way outside the guideline again, wide called.
wide yorker lands outside the guideline, wide called.
length ball on fifth stump, slapped wide of the sweeper for two.

dropped! Dube over short third man! Chahar goes for wide yorker again. Gowtham tries to heave this over midwicket and splices this off the toe swirling behind point. Dube jogs 15 yards along the ring but his feet are a bit tangled and he almost overruns this. As a result, his hands are in a tangle and not in a good position to reach for this coming back across his body. It clangs out badly. He made a straightforward chance look extremely difficult.
full and heaved to wide long-on, Stokes overruns the ball but a good backup by a teammate coming across from deep midwicket keeps this to two instead of four.
back of a length on the stumps, flicked to wide long-on for one.
slower bouncer on fifth stump, pulled to short fine leg for one.
full on middle, driven to wide midwicket for a sharp two.
back of a length on fifth stump, shuffles across to punch to long-on for one.
full on off, miscues a drive down the ground to long-off for one.
length ball on the stumps, flicked to the leg side for one.

full and wide on the guideline, slices a drive skied high toward Jadeja at point sweeper. If it was a World Cup or IPL Final, he'd have put in a dive but he stays on his feet after charging in and lets it short hop him for a single.
full and wide hugging the guideline, goes to drive and misses.
wide yorker, sprayed outside the guideline for another free extra.
full and wide, goes to drive and misses again as this one slides just inside the guideline.
full and outside the wide guideline, another wide called.
full and way outside the guideline, Gowtham drives hard at this but it's well out of reach. Wide called again.

shortText: Mohammed Shami to Warner, no run
text: Loud, loud appeal for a caught behind, but the umpire says no! There was some sound as the ball passed the bat. Did the ball hit the stumps? Oh, it did! What a ball from Shami. Length on off, shaping just a touch away from Warner, who pokes at it, and should have been a goner.
Good length ball with a bit of shape but way outside the tramline. Saha has to move to his left.
preText:
7.27pm The two umpires stride out to the middle. The two Delhi Capitals batters, Prithvi Shaw and David Warner, who is on 5973 IPL runs, also come out. The Titans fielders are in place. Mohammed Shami will take the new ball. Watch out for the nip-backer into Shaw. All set. Warner to take strike. Over the wicket. One slip in place.

Afeef: "Tough call to bench Rovman Powell "

Subs available for Titans: R Sai Kishore, Vijay Shankar, Jayant Yadav, Abhinav Manohar

Subs available for Capitals: Lalit Yadav, Rovman Powell, Chetan Sakariya, Manish Pandey, Khaleel Ahmed

Playing XIs

Gujarat Titans: WP Saha (wk), Shubman Gill, B Sai Sudharsan, HH Pandya (capt), DA Miller, R Tewatia, Rashid Khan, JB Little, AS Joseph, Yash Dayal, Mohammed Shami

Delhi Capitals P Shaw, DA Warner (capt), MR Marsh, SN Khan, RR Rossouw, Aman Hakim Khan, AR Patel, Abishek Porel, Kuldeep Yadav, A Nortje, Mukesh Kumar

Toss: David Warner has the coin. Hardik Pandya calls correctly and Titans will bowl first.

David Miller comes in for Williamson, while Sai Sudharsan replaces Vijay Shankar. For Delhi, Rovman Powell makes way for Anrich Nortje, while Abishek Porel gets his maiden DC cap.

Pandya: Losing Kane, we are gutted as a team but more for him. We have to move on and Miller comes back for Kane, and Sai Sudharsan comes in for Vijay Shankar. We didn't play our best cricket, but we still won in the first game. We just tried to keep things simple. That's something we are focusing on.

Warner: Looks like a nice wicket. We have to come out with a positive intent and put up a good score. [Homeground] Its awesome and hopefully we can put a good score for the crowd. Rovman is out. Abiskeh Porel comes on. Having another left-hander is crucial . There have neem a few harsh calls. We need to bat better, bowl better and field better than the opposition.

Toss in ten minutes. Changes expected in both sides. Both Miller and Nortje are warming up. Titans will have to replace Williamson who has been ruled out of the IPL with a right knee injury he had sustained in the opening game of the tournament. He has head back home for further assessment.

Satyajeet : "There is a certain Australian who is commentating in this IPL. He is a potential replacement for KW "

Dave: "Reeza Hendricks as Kane's replacement. He is in red hot form. "

Glanny: "Travid Head should be a suitable option. Can be used at the top or as an floater. Has recent experience on Indian pitches and can bowl a few handy overs in desperate situations. "

Here's Aaron Finch with his pitch report: The dimensions are 64 metres either side and 70 metres down the ground. It is the centre wicket. Not a blade of grass when the Test was played here, but there is a nice even covering of grass. Unbelievably flat wicket and I expect there to be a little more seam and carry for the fast bowlers. There are a couple of parts on the wicket that are very dry, they are still hard, though and they will not have a huge influence. 165 is the average score here. The trend so far in the IPL has been to chase, but personally, I would not be against batting first, putting a big total and then put pressure on the teams.

6.50pm In other news, KKR's Shreyas Iyer and RCB's Rajat Patidar have been ruled out of IPL 2023. Iyer will undergo surgery on his injured back and will therefore miss the entire 2023 IPL, and the World Test Championship (WTC) final in June. Patidar has been ruled out because of a heel injury.

Nirmal: "@Kataria: Hold our Hello says Buttler and Jaiswal"

Bhavin: "Ashish - have any potential Kane Williamson replacements been lined up by Gujarat?" Nothing at the moment. What are the potential options? Let us know in the comments.

6.45pm David Miller and Anrich Nortje have been spotted on the outfield, smiling away. Miller should come in straight for Kane Williamson, you'd expect. Nortje's pace should come handy on this Delhi surface. But who does he replace is the question.

Kataria: "@Vasanth: Hello Says Virat and Faf!"

Vasanth: "@Shrikant: Hello says Ruturaj and Conway"

6.40pm There was a Test match played between India and Australia not long back at this venue, one that saw the ball turning square from the first session and collapses galore. Certainly, the surface for this game will be expected to be much better for batters. Both sides are also waiting to see if their South Africans will be available: David Miller, Lungi Ngidi and Anrich Nortje were on the same flights from Johannesburg to Delhi, via Dubai. All this and more, in Matt Roller's preview.

Arun: "Ashish any news about the other Pant joining the DC dugout today ?" There was a bit of chatter about that the other day, but nothing concrete at the moment. We'll have to wait and watch, I suppose.

Shrikant: "Mark my words - Warner and Shaw will be the most successful opening pair in this IPL "

You can also follow live commentary of this match in Hindi here

6.30pm Hello and welcome to Match No.7 of IPL 2023, where we have Delhi Capitals taking on Gujarat Titans as Delhi return to their home territory. Both teams have had contrasting starts to their campaign. While Titans got the better of Chennai Super Kings by five wickets in the opener, Capitals were decimated by Mark Wood's fiery five-for in Lucknow. Can Capitals stage a comeback at home or will the defending champions continue their winning spree? This is Ashish Pant, and S Sudarshanan will soon join me as we bring to you all the updates from the Arun Jaitley Stadium.
